raphique: revue des publications épigraphiques relatives a l'antiquité romaine., 1888-","Manganaro, 1989, Iscrizioni Latine nuove e vecchie della Sicilia","Fasolo, 2013, Tyndaris e il suo territorio. Volume 1. Introduzione alla carta archeologica del territorio di Tindari",[226,227,228],"R46KDTZX","EZMBJ6GN","X2SEXMRX",[230,231,232,22,27,233,234,235,236,237,235,238,239,143],"isic000679","honours for publius septimius geta",{"_":5},"fine to medium-grained, homogeneous, grey, calcitic marble, likely proconnesian. optical microscopy: heteroblastic to homeoblastic fabric. digital microscopy: heteroblastic to homeoblastic fabric (identification based on pxrf, digital microscopy, xrd, optical microscopy)","tyndaris","tindari","sicilia","sicily","antiquarium di tindari","latin",[],{"title":242,"body":243,"divs":244,"editions":269,"images":279,"handnote":285},"ISic000679. Honours for Publius Septimius Geta","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Alex Antoniou, Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"la\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">...\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span> e]ṭ · \u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Publii · Septimi · Getae\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Publii\">P(ublii)\u003C/span> · \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Septimi\">Septimi\u003C/span> · \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Getae\">Gẹ[tae\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] ṛ(es) · p(ublica) · col(oniae) · Aug(ustae) · Ty[ndaritanorum] \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] d(ecreto) d(ecurionum) \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Alex Antoniou, Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">···\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>.].·\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Publii · Septimi · Getae\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Publii\">P\u003C/span>·\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Septimi\">SEPTIMI\u003C/span>·\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Getae\">G.[...\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>].·P·COL·AUG·TY[............]\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]DD\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000679_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2022-07-14\" src=\"ISic000679_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000679.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2022-07-14\" src=\"ISic000679-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text from autopsy\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"1\">1: \u003Cspan>Traces of the feet of three letters, one of them curved, but not readily identifiable\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"2\">2: \u003Cspan>The vertical at the start of the line is readily compatible with a T; there is a vertical preserved on the break at the end of the line.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-7077-0703\">Alex Antoniou\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>[?For the safety of ...] Publius Septimius Geta [...] The res publica of the colony of Augusta Tindaritani [erected this ...] by decree of the decurions\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Manganaro offers an extensive and speculative (if plausible) restoration on the model of ILS 433, along the lines of 'Pro salute imppp. Caesss. L. Septimi Severi - - - et M. Aureli Antonini et P. Septimi Getae - - - res publica colonia Augusta Tyndaritanorum P(ublica) P(ecunia) D(ecreto) D(ecurionum). It is indeed almost certain that this is a text erected jointly in honour of Septimius Severus and his two sons M. Aurelius (Caracalla) and P. Septimius Geta, but the exact form and date is unrecoverable. What is particularly notable is that the text has escaped damnatio memoriae of the name of Geta (at the orders of Caracalla, subsequent to his murder in December 211 CE) - indeed, ironically, Geta's name is the only part of this text to survive. Damnatio memoriae was also not observed in imperial honorific texts of the third-century from Halaesa, further along the north coast.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 1989.0338f \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manganaro 1989 163 no.10 fig.10 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001831\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001831\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Fasolo 2013 74-75 no.8 fig.38 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002011\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002011\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Deeply v-cut letters with serifs. Letters generally tend to the taller, thinner and slighly curved form. Upper horizontals curve up and away, P is sometimes open, L has a downward trailing foot, G has a very curved hook; Y in line 3 is much taller (58mm). Small triangular interpuncts.\u003C/p> Line 2-3  46-51  Line 4  25  Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[245,248,251,254,257,260,263,266],{"id":246,"html":247},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Alex Antoniou, Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"la\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">...\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span> e]ṭ · \u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Publii · Septimi · Getae\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Publii\">P(ublii)\u003C/span> · \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Septimi\">Septimi\u003C/span> · \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Getae\">Gẹ[tae\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] ṛ(es) · p(ublica) · col(oniae) · Aug(ustae) · Ty[ndaritanorum] \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] d(ecreto) d(ecurionum) \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Alex Antoniou, Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">···\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>.].·\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Publii · Septimi · Getae\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Publii\">P\u003C/span>·\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Septimi\">SEPTIMI\u003C/span>·\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Getae\">G.[...\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>].·P·COL·AUG·TY[............]\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]DD\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":249,"html":250},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000679_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2022-07-14\" src=\"ISic000679_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000679.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2022-07-14\" src=\"ISic000679-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>",{"id":252,"html":253},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text from autopsy\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"1\">1: \u003Cspan>Traces of the feet of three letters, one of them curved, but not readily identifiable\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"2\">2: \u003Cspan>The vertical at the start of the line is readily compatible with a T; there is a vertical preserved on the break at the end of the line.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":255,"html":256},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-7077-0703\">Alex Antoniou\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>[?For the safety of ...] Publius Septimius Geta [...] The res publica of the colony of Augusta Tindaritani [erected this ...] by decree of the decurions\u003C/p>  ",{"id":258,"html":259},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Manganaro offers an extensive and speculative (if plausible) restoration on the model of ILS 433, along the lines of 'Pro salute imppp. Caesss. L. Septimi Severi - - - et M. Aureli Antonini et P. Septimi Getae - - - res publica colonia Augusta Tyndaritanorum P(ublica) P(ecunia) D(ecreto) D(ecurionum). It is indeed almost certain that this is a text erected jointly in honour of Septimius Severus and his two sons M. Aurelius (Caracalla) and P. Septimius Geta, but the exact form and date is unrecoverable. What is particularly notable is that the text has escaped damnatio memoriae of the name of Geta (at the orders of Caracalla, subsequent to his murder in December 211 CE) - indeed, ironically, Geta's name is the only part of this text to survive. Damnatio memoriae was also not observed in imperial honorific texts of the third-century from Halaesa, further along the north coast.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":261,"html":262},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 1989.0338f \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manganaro 1989 163 no.10 fig.10 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001831\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001831\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Fasolo 2013 74-75 no.8 fig.38 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002011\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002011\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":264,"html":265},"handnote","\u003Cp>Deeply v-cut letters with serifs. Letters generally tend to the taller, thinner and slighly curved form. Upper horizontals curve up and away, P is sometimes open, L has a downward trailing foot, G has a very curved hook; Y in line 3 is much taller (58mm). Small triangular interpuncts.\u003C/p> Line 2-3  46-51  Line 4  25  Interlineation line 1 to 2    ",{"id":267,"html":268},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[270,272,275,276],{"html":271},"Text encoding: Alex Antoniou, Jonathan Prag",{"id":273,"lang":143,"html":274},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">...\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span> e]ṭ · \u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Publii · Septimi · Getae\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Publii\">P(ublii)\u003C/span> · \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Septimi\">Septimi\u003C/span> · \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Getae\">Gẹ[tae\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] ṛ(es) · p(ublica) · col(oniae) · Aug(ustae) · Ty[ndaritanorum] \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] d(ecreto) d(ecurionum) \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"html":271},{"id":277,"lang":143,"html":278},"edition-diplomatic","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">···\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>.].·\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Publii · Septimi · Getae\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Publii\">P\u003C/span>·\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Septimi\">SEPTIMI\u003C/span>·\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Getae\">G.[...\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>].·P·COL·AUG·TY[............]\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]DD\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",[280,282],{"image":118,"thumb":281,"title":121},"ISic000679_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":283,"thumb":284,"title":121},"ISic000679.jpg","ISic000679-thumb.jpg",[286],{"html":68},"\u003C?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"https://epidoc.stoa.org/schema/latest/tei-epidoc.rng\" type=\"application/xml\" schematypens=\"http://relaxng.org/ns/structure/1.0\"?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"../schematron/ircyr-checking.sch\" schematypens=\"http://purl.oclc.org/dsdl/schematron\"?>\n\u003CTEI xmlns=\"http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\" xml:lang=\"en\">\n    \u003CteiHeader>\n        \u003CfileDesc>\n            \u003CtitleStmt>\n                \u003Ctitle>Honours for Publius Septimius Geta\u003C/title>\n                \u003Ceditor ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/editor>\n                \u003Cprincipal ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/principal>\n                \u003Cfunder>John Fell OUP Research Fund\u003C/funder>\n\t   \u003Cfunder>\u003Cref target=\"https://cordis.europa.eu/project/id/885040\">ERC Advanced Grant no.885040\u003C/ref>\u003C/funder>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"JP\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>original data collection and editing\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"JCu\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6686-3728\">James Cummings\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>conversion to EpiDoc\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n        \t    \u003CrespStmt>\n         \t       \u003Cname xml:id=\"SS\" ref=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3914-9569\">Simona Stoyanova\u003C/name>\n         \t       \u003Cresp>standardisation of template and tidying up encoding\u003C/resp>\n         \t   \u003C/respStmt>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"AA\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-7077-0703\">Alex Antoniou\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>EpiDoc editing and English translation\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n            \u003C/titleStmt>\n            \u003CpublicationStmt>\n                \u003Cauthority>I.Sicily\u003C/authority>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"filename\">ISic000679\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"TM\">175745\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDR\">081488\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDH\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDCS\">6100253\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"PHI\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"URI\">http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000679\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"DOI\" when=\"2020-12-22\">10.5281/zenodo.4385150\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cavailability>\n                    \u003Clicence target=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/\">Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.\u003C/licence>\n                \u003C/availability>\n            \u003C/publicationStmt>\n            \u003CsourceDesc>\n                \u003CmsDesc>\n                    \u003CmsIdentifier>\n                        \u003Ccountry>Italy\u003C/country>\n                        \u003Cregion>Sicily\u003C/region>\n                        \u003Csettlement>Tindari\u003C/settlement>\n                        \u003Crepository role=\"museum\" ref=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/052\">Antiquarium di Tindari\u003C/repository>\n                        \u003Cidno type=\"inventory\">ME 28744\u003C/idno>\n                        \u003C!--Adding location for old id numbers if available-->\n                        \u003CaltIdentifier>\n                            \u003Csettlement>Tindari\u003C/settlement>\n                            \u003Crepository>Antiquarium di Tindari\u003C/repository>\n                            \u003Cidno type=\"old\">804\u003C/idno>\n                        \u003C/altIdentifier>\n                    \u003C/msIdentifier>\n                    \u003CmsContents>\n                        \u003CtextLang mainLang=\"la\">Latin\u003C/textLang>\n                    \u003C/msContents>\n                    \u003CphysDesc>\n                        \u003CobjectDesc>\n                            \u003CsupportDesc>\n                                \u003Csupport>\u003Cp>Fragment of a thick grey marble plaque, intact along the lower edge, but broken on the other three sides. The lower edge is chipped, and the edge itself only roughly finished. The rear is finished smooth.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Cmaterial ana=\"#material.stone.marble\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html\">marble\u003C/material>\n                                    \u003CobjectType ana=\"#object.plaque\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259.html\">plaque\u003C/objectType>\n                                    \u003Cdimensions>\n                                        \u003Cheight unit=\"cm\">19.8\u003C/height>\n                                        \u003Cwidth unit=\"cm\">22.5\u003C/width>\n                                        \u003Cdepth unit=\"cm\">2.8-3.6 (right to left)\u003C/depth>\n                                    \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003C/support>\n                                \u003Ccondition ana=\"#condition.fragment\"/>\n\t\t    \u003C/supportDesc>\n                            \u003ClayoutDesc>\n                                \u003Clayout>\u003Cp>Traces of four lines of Latin letters, guidelines are visible top and bottom of line 3; line four is much smaller.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Crs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled\u003C/rs>\n                                \t\u003Cdamage ana=\"#text_condition.incomplete\"/>\n\t\t\t\u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\u003Cp>Deeply v-cut letters with serifs. Letters generally tend to the taller, thinner and slighly curved form. Upper horizontals curve up and away, P is sometimes open, L has a downward trailing foot, G has a very curved hook; Y in line 3 is much taller (58mm). Small triangular interpuncts.\u003C/p>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line2\" to=\"line3\">Line 2-3\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"46\" atMost=\"51\">46-51\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line4\" to=\"line4\">Line 4\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"25\" atMost=\"25\">25\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\"/>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                            \u003C/handNote>\n                        \u003C/handDesc>\n                    \u003C/physDesc>\n                    \u003Chistory>\n                        \u003Corigin>\n                            \u003CorigPlace>\u003Cregion>Sicilia\u003C/region>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462527\">Tyndaris\u003C/placeName>\t\t\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/10282151\">Tindari\u003C/placeName>\n                            \t\u003Cgeo>38.14227, 15.04385\u003C/geo>\n\t\t\u003C/origPlace>\n                            \u003CorigDate datingMethod=\"#julian\" notBefore-custom=\"0198\" notAfter-custom=\"0211\">Presumably to fall within the period of Geta as either Caesar (from 198) or Augustus (209) and his death in late 211.\u003C/origDate>\n                        \u003C/origin>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"found\" subtype=\"discovered\">From the site of Tindari, but details of provenance not recorded.\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"observed\" subtype=\"autopsied\" resp=\"#JP\">Prag, 2022-07-12, in the antiquarium\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cacquisition/>\n                    \u003C/history>\n                \u003C/msDesc>\n            \u003C/sourceDesc>\n        \u003C/fileDesc>\n        \u003CencodingDesc>\n             \u003Cp>Encoded following the latest EpiDoc guidelines\u003C/p>\n             \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/ISicily-taxonomies.xml\">\n                 \u003Cxi:fallback>\n                     \u003Cp>Taxonomies for ISicily controlled values\u003C/p>\n                 \u003C/xi:fallback>\n             \u003C/xi:include>\n\t  \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/charDecl.xml\">\n\t     \u003Cxi:fallback>\n\t       \u003Cp>ISicily glyphs authority list\u003C/p>\n\t     \u003C/xi:fallback>\n\t   \u003C/xi:include>\n         \u003C/encodingDesc>\n        \u003CprofileDesc>\n            \u003CcalendarDesc>\n                \u003Ccalendar xml:id=\"julian\">\n                    \u003Cp>Julian Calendar\u003C/p>\n                \u003C/calendar>\n            \u003C/calendarDesc>\n            \u003ClangUsage>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"en\">English\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"it\">Italian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"la\">Latin\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"he\">Hebrew\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"phn\">Phoenician\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xpu\">Punic\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"osc\">Oscan\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xly\">Elymian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"scx\">Sikel\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"sxc\">Sikan\u003C/language>\n            \u003C/langUsage>\n            \u003CtextClass>\n                \u003Ckeywords scheme=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins.html\">\n                    \u003Cterm ana=\"#function.honorific\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/69.html\">honorific\u003C/term>\n                \u003C/keywords>\n            \u003C/textClass>\n        \u003C/profileDesc>\n        \u003CrevisionDesc status=\"edited\">\n            \u003ClistChange>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2016-12-03\" who=\"#JCu\">James Cummings autogenerated EpiDoc output from database\u003C/change>\n            \t\u003Cchange when=\"2020-10-05\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova normalised Unicode\u003C/change>\n            \t\u003Cchange when=\"2020-10-08\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova updated list of languages\u003C/change>\n            \t\u003Cchange when=\"2020-11-20\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova added EDCS numbers\u003C/change>\n        \t\t\u003Cchange when=\"2020-11-26\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova restructured bibliography\u003C/change>\n        \t    \u003Cchange when=\"2020-12-22\" who=\"#JP\">Updated Zenodo DOI\u003C/change>\n            \t\u003Cchange when=\"2021-01-19\" who=\"#SS\">renumbered files, uris and references\u003C/change>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2021-05-06\" who=\"#AA\">Epidoc editing and English translation\u003C/change>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2026-03-06\" who=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag revised from autopsy\u003C/change>\n\t\u003C/listChange>\n        \u003C/revisionDesc>\n    \u003C/teiHeader>\n    \u003Cfacsimile>\n        \u003Csurface type=\"front\">\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic000679_tiled.tif\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2022-07-14\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic000679.jpg\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2022-07-14\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n         \u003C/surface>\n    \u003C/facsimile>\n    \u003Ctext>\n        \u003Cbody>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"edition\" subtype=\"primary\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xml:lang=\"la\" resp=\"#AA #JP\">\n                \u003Cab>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"1\"/>\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/>\u003Cgap reason=\"illegible\" unit=\"character\" quantity=\"3\"/>\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"2\"/>\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/> \u003Csupplied reason=\"lost\">e\u003C/supplied>\u003Cunclear>t\u003C/unclear> \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> \u003CpersName type=\"attested\">\u003Cname>\u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>P\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>ublii\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan>\u003C/name> \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> \u003Cname>Septimi\u003C/name> \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> \u003Cname>G\u003Cunclear>e\u003C/unclear>\u003Csupplied reason=\"lost\">tae\u003C/supplied>\u003C/name>\u003C/persName> \u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"3\"/>\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/> \u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>\u003Cunclear>r\u003C/unclear>\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>es\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan> \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> \u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>p\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>ublica\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan> \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> \u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>col\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>oniae\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan> \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> \u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>Aug\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>ustae\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan> \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> \u003CplaceName type=\"ethnic\">Ty\u003Csupplied reason=\"lost\">ndaritanorum\u003C/supplied>\u003C/placeName>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"4\"/>\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/> \u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>d\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>ecreto\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan> \u003CroleName type=\"civic\" subtype=\"decurio\">\u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>d\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>ecurionum\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan>\u003C/roleName>\n                \u003C/ab>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"apparatus\">\n                \u003ClistApp>\n                    \u003Capp>\u003Cnote>Text from autopsy\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n                    \u003Capp loc=\"1\">\u003Cnote>Traces of the feet of three letters, one of them curved, but not readily identifiable\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n                    \u003Capp loc=\"2\">\u003Cnote>The vertical at the start of the line is readily compatible with a T; there is a vertical preserved on the break at the end of the line.\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n                \u003C/listApp>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"translation\" xml:lang=\"en\" resp=\"#AA\">\n                \u003Cp>[?For the safety of ...] Publius Septimius Geta [...] The res publica of the colony of Augusta Tindaritani [erected this ...] by decree of the decurions\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"commentary\">\n                \u003Cp>Manganaro offers an extensive and speculative (if plausible) restoration on the model of ILS 433, along the lines of 'Pro salute imppp. Caesss. L. Septimi Severi - - - et M. Aureli Antonini et P. Septimi Getae - - - res publica colonia Augusta Tyndaritanorum P(ublica) P(ecunia) D(ecreto) D(ecurionum). It is indeed almost certain that this is a text erected jointly in honour of Septimius Severus and his two sons M. Aurelius (Caracalla) and P. Septimius Geta, but the exact form and date is unrecoverable. What is particularly notable is that the text has escaped damnatio memoriae of the name of Geta (at the orders of Caracalla, subsequent to his murder in December 211 CE) - indeed, ironically, Geta's name is the only part of this text to survive. Damnatio memoriae was also not observed in imperial honorific texts of the third-century from Halaesa, further along the north coast.\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"bibliography\">\n                \u003ClistBibl type=\"edition\">\n                    \u003Cbibl type=\"bulletin\" n=\"AE\">\n                        \u003CcitedRange>1989.0338f\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/R46KDTZX\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Manganaro\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>1989\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>163 no.10 fig.10\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/EZMBJ6GN\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001831\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001831\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Fasolo\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>2013\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>74-75 no.8 fig.38\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/X2SEXMRX\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002011\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002011\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                \u003C/listBibl>\n\t   \u003ClistBibl type=\"discussion\">\u003Cbibl/>\u003C/listBibl>\n            \u003C/div>\n        \u003C/body>\n    \u003C/text>\n\u003C/TEI>\n"],"uses":{"params":["slug"]}}]}
